SOLD THE NEW ONE ~~ but have the other one !!!    Early Eastern Bloc AK-47 Bayonet and Scabbard new unissued condition.   These were some of the first AK-47 Bayonets issued for Russian, Bulgarian, Polish, Romanian, etc.

The AK47 Bayonet

The AK47 assault rifle was introduced during a period where the bayonet's future was in debate. In the decade following the outbreak of the Second World War, most of the major powers produced an infantry rifle without the ability to mount a bayonet. Without a single exception, every one was redesigned to accept a bayonet or or replaced with a rifle that did within a few years of its introduction. The AK47 was Russia's entry in the bayonet debate, being designed without a bayonet lug. Rather than add a bayonet lug, the Russians opted for a bayonet that did not require one. The AK47 hilt design borrows heavily from the Swedish M1914 bayonet, another example where the bayonet was an afterthought. The blade was patterned after the the Russian M1940 bayonet for the 7.62 mm. Tokarev SVT–40 self–loading rifle. Although adequate as a bayonet, the dual muzzle-ring arrangement made the AK47 bayonet awkward, at best, for any other uses. The scabbard is a smaller version of the later type used with the Russian M1940 bayonet.

This rifle retails for $2300.00 SR-15 IWS E3 CARBINE MOD 2 The Knight’s Armament Company SR-15 line represents the pinnacle of firearms based upon the Eugene Stoner designed operating system. The Mod 2’s 16” chrome lined, 5.56mm NATO barrel is manufactured to military specifications, and features a proprietary mid-length gas system that increases reliability and durability while also reducing felt recoil. An improved E3 round-lug bolt design both enhances function and increases bolt life far beyond the industry standard. An ambidextrous bolt release, selector, and magazine release offer left-handed users the ergonomic advantages inherent to AR15-based controls, as well as giving right-handed users alternative methods of manipulation to increase efficiency of movement. The drop-in two-stage trigger serves double duty as an aid to long range precision marksmanship while enabling surgical speed shooting at close range. The Mod 2 update introduces several notable features to the SR15 IWS line: a URX4 handguard with Keymod accessory mounting points for-ancillary device attachments increases cooling characteristics and reduces weight and bulk compared with standard 1913 rail attachment methods. A Mod 2 gas system with a proprietary design minimizes leakage and ensures more consistent operation in harsh conditions. A gas block secured with a locking ring instead of taper pins increases barrel rigidity and eliminates the need to custom fit the gas block to the barrel. Included parts and features, such as the two-sided receiver end plate QD sling swivel mounting point, collapsible six-position SOPMOD stock, hybrid ambidextrous selector lever, and folding 200-600 meter sights, round out the package to deliver a cutting-edge carbine right out of the case.

title: For Sale:  Kimber Mountain Ascent 270
postcontent:
Kimber Mountain Ascent in .270 Winchester.  

Lightweight for Colorado Mountains – only weighs 5 lbs 5 oz!! 

Extremely accurate – shoots Hornady Whitetail 130 grain factory ammunition ($21 per box) into .6 inch groups at 3,075 fps.  Shoots handloads of 150 grain Nosler Accubond long-range bullets at 3,000 fps into .8 inch groups. (1533 ft lbs of kinetic energy at 750 yards)

The action and barrel are stainless, but Weaver Rifles recoated/painted the stock in tan with black webbing and ceramic coated all the metal a non-reflective graphite black.

The 24-inch barrel has a screw-on muzzle cap and an effective muzzle brake is included for use at the range.  Includes all paperwork, factory accessories, and the box.

I used this rifle for one elk and mule deer hunt here in Colorado and killed five white tails in Missouri with it.  It is accurate and extremely light.  I hardly noticed it in my tree stand in Missouri or on the daily mountain climb in Colorado.  

The scope is a Leupold VX-III 4.5x14.  I will sell it and the rifle together for $1,850  or the rifle by itself, including the rings, for $1,550.  

I paid $550 for the scope new and $2,250 for the rifle and paint/cerakote.

title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense DDMK18 10.5 Upper Reciever W/Extras
location: Southwest Durham, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
-About The Item-

Lightly used Daniel Defense MK18 10.5 Factory Complete Upper Receiver with DD Bolt Carrier Group, Noveske KX3 Flash Hider, original DD Flash Hider, Magpul BUIS Front and Rear as well as the original box. Originally purchased for an AR pistol build that I wanted to eventually register and convert to an SBR, however due to the fact my wife is making me sell excess toys for an upcoming Home Purchase, my dreams of a sweet MK18 clone are now essentially dead. This upper has only been on an AR pistol lower with less than 100 rounds down the barrel. 

-About The Law-

Very important section regarding legalities: ALL NFA RULES APPLY. That's it. It is your responsibility to know the law, and to follow the law because in all seriousness I am not a lawyer, I do not play one on TV, and I certainly will not play one in real life on the internet. Research and make a responsible decision to follow the law.

If you don't know what the NFA is, you are probably new here, in which case - welcome, we have all been waiting for you. Allow me to be the one man welcoming committee tasked with the ever important job of keeping you safe from the very real risk of becoming a very bad person. The NFA protects us all from devices known as Short Barreled Rifles (SBR's), Machine Guns, Destructive Devices, "Silencers", Any Other Weapons (AOW's) and pretty much any other cool thing that lowly civilians such as ourselves could never possibly be trusted with..... That is, unless of course, you happen to have $200 that you could make payable in the form of a check to the ATF,  a pen to fill out an ATF Form 4/1, and the patience to wait 9-14 months for the return of your approved Form 4/1, because if you did - congratulations, my new friend, you have joined an elite super group of citizens deemed worthy enough to have one of the aforementioned cool things I just listed out for you. 

However, (this is the most important part) IF YOU DID NOT DO ALL OF THOSE THINGS, you cannot have/build or posses components with the intent to manufacture those cool devices I told you about. If you do, you do it at your own, very significant risk and you are probably an idiot. The ATF does not mess around, and neither do I, so please read and understand the law. This will get you started.

 https://www.atf.gov/firearms/faq/national-firearms-act-firearms.html

-About The Transaction-   

With all that said, I am Asking $900.00, Photo ID and your signature on a piece of paper that basically says you understand the NFA and that you are purchasing this upper. Before you freak out, I am not the NSA, and I have read 1984. I am doing this because lawyers exist and because I prefer to cover my ass when I sell things. 

Why all the other stuff? Because I want to be sure this item is sold with the full understanding that depending on your intent, this item could get you in trouble. 

Will I ship to other states you ask? No.

 I will entertain realistic and/or respectable offers. (Read: I don't want your mother's second ex husband's old Mosin Nagant, I certainly would not like that $50 Gift card to Applebee's with the Christmas tree on it you got from that awkward guy at the office that you don't really like who keeps giving you things in the hopes you'll add him on linkedin, or, whatever, and I don't need handyman services, because really I don't.) 

The ARMSLIST regulars know what I am talking about there. 

-About the Lister-

Don't let my listing fool you, I'm like Mr. Rogers, except nicer. I sell stuff on here occasionally when my wife tells me to (because she's just hot as hell and cooks better than I do so I kinda have a lot to lose in that department) and the people on here can be pretty ridiculous when it comes to offers. I care about you. Buy my stuff.

Machined from 8620 steel with a black oxide finish and heat treated for a life of hard use, the Manticore Arms Yugo M92 NightBrake muzzle compensator is designed specifically for the 26x1.5 left hand thread found on the muzzle of the Yugoslavian M92 and M85 Krinkov rifles and PAP series of pistols.

The NightBrake is designed to reduce felt recoil and virtually eliminate muzzle rise, and can safely pass any projectile up to 0.311" (0.30 caliber) in diameter, making it a universal muzzle device fro both the M85 and M92.

A total of eighteen ports distributed around the uppper 270 arc of the device help stabilize and reduce exiting gas pressure.  There are no ports facing directly upwards to minimize flash in the line of sight, and the lower 90 degree arc has no ports to precent a dust signature when fired.

The Yugo M92 NightBrake flash hider is 2.125" inches long, adding only 1.125" to the overall length of the rifle- it is over an inch shorter than the standard M92 muzzle booster!
